<Author>CK3Fam
<Content>Just What We Were Looking For! We chose this hotel on a recommendation from the bride and groom of the wedding we were in town for. They picked a central location to the rehearsal site, wedding, and the reception. We have never stayed at an Embassy Suites. We loved it!We were immediately greeted by energetic staff. Before we even took our bags upstairs we were told about the Manager's 'Happy Hour.' Free appetizers, wine, liquor and beer every day from 5:30pm - 7:30pm! It was a nice treat to grab a drink before heading to our room or out to dinner.Complimentary, cooked-to-order breakfast every morning too! Omelets, pancakes, bacon, sausage, hashbrowns, pastries, cereal, coffee, tea, etc. They even had a fountain drink machine...I've never had complimentary breakfast that served me my Diet Coke!!!Large open atrium in the center of the hotel with the rooms circling around. I didn't think it was noisy like other reviews stated. Maybe you could request a higher level room. They have a 24 hours store in the lobby that sells snacks and toiletries. There is also a 24 CVS pharmacy practically in the same parking lot, which was very convenient. A few other notes: Courtesy shuttle will take you where you need to go; The Galleria is obviously very close; The lobby has a kiosk that allows you to check-in/check-out at the hotel and check-in for your flight; Rooms were spacious and clean; Room Service is available.Everyone in our group really enjoyed our stay! 
