<Author>NewEnglandCamper
<Content>Embassy Suites in Dallas - Typical Stay I only stayed 1 night at the Embassy Suites in Dallas (near the Galleria) for a business trip.Memorable items:* The suite was VERY spacious, large, and clean (two tvs which I didn't watch either). The King size bed was VERY comfortable.* Loved the happy hour with FREE snacks and FREE adult beverages while socializing with my colleagues.* Loved the FREE HOT breakfast the following morning with made to order omlet * The Steak Burger and fries that I ordered from the on-site resturant was AWESOME and affordable when compared to other hotel foodThe only complaints are the following.* High speed internet cost $10 (when most other hotels give this to you for free) * There were very small little ants in running around in my bathroom. This did not prevent me from using it but my wife would have demanded another room * I didn't care for the Swans in the hotel. They should be in a park vs. a hotel. 
