<Author>UnitedStatesfan
<Content>Poor public relations I made reservations to this hotel on 7/15/07 for a four night stay starting November 16th, 2007. (confirmation Number 83470977)After finalizing my travel plans and buying airlione tickets I called the hotel directly to change my check in date to November 17th, 2007. This was done in September 2007. I also advised the staff that I would be a late arrival since our flight did not get into Dallas until 11:30 pm and by the time I got my luggage and rental car it would probably be between 12:00am and 1:00am. I was assured that the late arrival would not be a problem and that the non-smoking room with two doubles would be available. On the morning of my flight I again called the hotel to remind the staff of my late arrival. I was again told that my room would be available. My family of five arrived at the hotel at 1:00 am. I was told by the night manager that they only had one room available and that it was a smoking room. Since my 7 year old has allergies and is sensitive to smoke I asked the manager if anything could be done to get a different room. He said that the smoking room was the only one available. Because it was already late I decided to check the room to see if it was at least clean enough to stay for the night until another room would be availabe the following day. When I was shown the room, it reeked of cigarette smoke. The room was dark and dingy and felt like a cave. The furnishings were old and soiled. I told the manager that the room was not acceptable. He said that he was sorry but that was the best that he could do. I asked if I could use the hotel phone to look for another hotel. He told me that I had to use the pay phone. When I went to the pay phone, there was no phone book. I asked the manger for a phone book and he said that he did not have one. I remembered passing a Hyatt Place one block away. I called the hotel and they had a room available for less than what I was paying at the Embassy Suites. This is where we ended up staying for the trip. It was a newly remodeled hotel with oversized rooms and a 42 inch flat panel TV. I was dissapointed with the Embassy Suies managment for not even attempting to find me a room with another Hilton family hotel for my stay and did not seem to care that they had over booked their rooms. I returned the next two days to talk Carol Chandler, the general manager but each time I was told that she was not in. I also left my cell phone number for her to call and she never did. If you are looking for a hotel near the Galleria in Dallas Texas I highly recommend the Hyatt Place which is a two minute walk to the Galleria, and not the Embassy Suites on Noel Road. 
